{"hadithnumber": "146", "text": "“Allah’s Messenger said (Allah bless him and give him peace): ‘What an excellent condiment vinegar is'!”"}
{"hadithnumber": "147", "text": "“Do you not have what you want in the way of food and drink? I have seen your Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace), and the poor-quality dates  that he finds are what fills his stomach."}
{"hadithnumber": "148", "text": "Allah’s Messenger said (Allah bless him and give him peace): 'What an excellent condiment vinegar is!’”"}
{"hadithnumber": "149", "text": "We were in the presence of Abu Musa al- Ash'ari when he was brought some chicken meat. A man among the people thereupon turned away, so he asked him: 'What is the matter?' He replied: 'I saw it eating something putrid, so I swore that I would not eat it.' He  said: 'Draw near, for I have seen Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and\\ngive him peace) eating the meat of chickens'!”"}
{"hadithnumber": "150", "text": "I ate together with Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) the meat of a bustard.”"}
{"hadithnumber": "151", "text": "We were in the presence of Abu Musa al-Ash'ari. Among the people there was a man from the Banu Taimi’llah, ruddy as if he were a freed slave, and he did not draw near, so Abu Musa said to him: 'Draw near, for I saw Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give\\nhim peace) eat some of it,' but he said: 'I saw it eat something and I found it loathsome, so I swore that I would never taste it'!”"}
{"hadithnumber": "152", "text": "“Allah’s Messenger said (Allah bless him and give him peace): ‘Eat  oil, and anoint with it, for it is from a blessed tree!’”"}
{"hadithnumber": "153", "text": "“Allah’s Messenger said (Allah bless him and give him peace): ‘Eat oil, and anoint with it, for it is from a blessed tree'!”"}
{"hadithnumber": "154", "text": "Another chain reports similar to the previous narration and it did not mention \"related from 'Umar (RA)"}
{"hadithnumber": "155", "text": "“The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) used to admire the gourd, so when he was brought a meal or invited to one, I would seek it out and set it in front of him, because I knew that he liked it.”"}
{"hadithnumber": "156", "text": "I entered the presence of the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace), and I saw beside him a gourd being carved into pieces, so I said: 'What is this?' He said: 'We use it to augment our meal'."}
{"hadithnumber": "157", "text": "“A tailor invited Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) to a meal he had made, so I went with Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) to that meal. He presented Allah's Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) with some barley-bread and broth containing a gourd and jerked meat. Then I saw the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) looking for chunks of gourd all around the bowl, and and I've loved gourd ever since.”"}
{"hadithnumber": "158", "text": "The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) used to love sweets and honey.”"}
{"hadithnumber": "159", "text": "Umm Salama informed 'Ata ibn Yasar that she served Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) a grilled flank, so he ate from it, then embarked on the ritual prayer and did not perform the minor ritual ablution."}
{"hadithnumber": "160", "text": "Together with Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace), we ate grilled meat in the mosque.”"}
{"hadithnumber": "161", "text": "“I was a guest one night together with Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace), so he was brought a grilled flank. Then he took the blade and set about carving, and he carved some for me. Bilal arrived calling him to prayer, so he threw the blade away, and he said: ‘Why have his hands been soiled?’ His mustache hung down close to his mouth, so he said to him: ‘I shall clip it for you over a tooth-stick,’ or: ‘Clip it over a tooth-stick'!”"}
{"hadithnumber": "162", "text": "‘The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) was brought some meat, so the foreleg was set before him, and he liked it, so he took a bite of it.”"}
{"hadithnumber": "163", "text": "The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) used to like the foreleg  also said: \"He was poisoned with a foreleg, however, as he used to believe that the Jews had poisoned him.”"}
{"hadithnumber": "164", "text": "I cooked a dish for the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace), and he used to take great pleasure in the foreleg ,so I passed him the foreleg. Then he said: 'Pass me the foreleg,' so I passed it to him. Then he said: 'Pass me the foreleg,' so I said: 'O Messenger of Allah, how many forelegs does a sheep have?' He said: 'By the One in whose Hand is my soul, if you kept silent, you would surely pass me the foreleg whenever I asked for it!’”"}
{"hadithnumber": "165", "text": "“The foreleg was not the meat dearest to Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace), but he only got to have meat occasionally, so he would rush to it, because it was the part that got done the most quickly.”"}
{"hadithnumber": "166", "text": "“I heard Allah’s Messenger say (Allah bless him and give him peace): ‘The best of the meat is the back'.”"}
{"hadithnumber": "167", "text": "The Prophet said (Allah bless him and give him peace): 'What an excellent condiment vinegar is'!”"}
{"hadithnumber": "168", "text": "The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) entered my presence and said: 'Do you have anything in your possession?' I said: 'No, apart from some dry bread and vinegar', so he said: 'Give me some! A household in which there is vinegar is not devoid of seasoning'!”"}
{"hadithnumber": "169", "text": "“The superiority of 'Aisha over all other women is like the superiority of tharid  over all other food.”"}
{"hadithnumber": "170", "text": "“Allah’s Messenger said (Allah bless him and give him peace):‘The superiority of 'A'isha over all other women is like the superiority of tharid  over all other food'.”"}
{"hadithnumber": "171", "text": "Abu Huraira (may Allah be well pleased with him) said that he saw Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) perform the minor ritual ablution because of eating cottage cheese. Then he saw him eat from the flank of a sheep, and then perform the ritual prayer without performing the minor ritual ablution."}
{"hadithnumber": "172", "text": "Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) gave a wedding banquet for Safiyya consisting of dried dates and parched barley.”"}
{"hadithnumber": "173", "text": "Make us a meal consisting of that which used to delight Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace), and which used to make his food more palatable!\" She replied: ‘O my dear son, do not wish for it today!’ He said: ‘Oh yes, you must make it for us!’ She therefore got up, took some barley and ground it. Then she put it into a pot, poured some oil over it, crushed the pepper and the spices, and presented it to them. She said: \"This is some of that which used to delight Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace), and which used to make his food \\nmore palatable!”"}
{"hadithnumber": "174", "text": "“The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) came to us in our house, so we slaughtered a sheep for him, and he said: ‘It is as if they knew that we love meat'!\" (This\\ntradition is part of a longer story)."}
{"hadithnumber": "175", "text": "“Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) went out and I went with him, then he went in to see a woman from among the Helpers , so she slaughtered a sheep for him and he ate some of it. She also brought him a dish of ripe dates, and he ate some of them. Then he performed the minor ritual ablution for the noon prayer, and performed it. Then he departed, and she\\nbrought him a leftover from the remnant of the sheep, and he ate. Then he performed the afternoon ritual prayer but did not perform the minor ritual ablution.”"}
{"hadithnumber": "176", "text": "“Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) came to see me with 'Ali. We had some suspended clusters of grapes, so Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) started to eat, and 'Ali was eating with him. Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) therefore said to 'Ali: ‘Take it easy, O ‘Ali, for you are a convalescent!’ So 'Ali sat down while the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) ate, and I offered them some chard and barley. The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) said to 'Ali: ‘Eat some of this, for this is more appropriate for you'!”"}
{"hadithnumber": "177", "text": "The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) used to come to me and say: “Do you have something for lunch?” I would say: “No,” so he would say: “I am fasting.” When he came to me one day, I said: “O Messenger of Allah, we have been given a gift!” He said: “What is it?” I said: “It is a meal of dates mixed with butter and curds.” He said: “As for me,\\nI began the day fasting.” But then he ate.”"}
{"hadithnumber": "178", "text": "“I saw the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) take a slice of barley-bread. Then he put a dried date on it and said: ‘This is the condiment for this,’ and he ate it.”"}
{"hadithnumber": "179", "text": "He used to like the dregs .” 'Abdullah said: “That means what is left over from the meal.”"}
